The paper discusses a process for reviewing commercial spreadsheets to ensure they can be safely modified without introducing new errors. This involves examining the structure and logic of the spreadsheet, as well as testing it with various inputs and scenarios. This process is relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including software engineering (cs.SE), programming languages (cs.PL), cybernetics (cs.CY), cryptography (cs.CR), and human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
